HEADWORD: Elaterium
<hw>El`a*te"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/, neut. of <?/ driving. See 2d <er>Elater</er>.]</ety> <def>A
cathartic substance obtained, in the form of yellowish or greenish
cakes, as the dried residue of the juice of the wild or squirting
